Wash and dry produce. Quarter @Lime{1}. Core, deseed, and dice @Poblano Pepper{1}. Drain and rinse @Black Beans{13.4%oz}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Sour Cream{4%tbsp} with a big squeeze of lime juice to taste. Stir in water @water{1%tsp} at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Melt @Butter{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add poblano and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add beans and @Tex-Mex Paste{1}; season with salt and pepper. Cook until beans are warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #medium bowl{}. Wash out pan.

Place @Flour Tortillas{2} on a clean work surface; evenly top one half of each tortilla with half the @Monterey Jack Cheese{1%cup}. Top with filling, then sprinkle with remaining Monterey Jack. Fold tortillas in half to create quesadillas.

Melt @Butter{1%tbsp} in pan used for filling over medium-high heat. (For 4 servings, you may need to work in batches, using 1 TBSP butter for each batch.) Add quesadillas; cook until tortillas are golden brown and cheese melts, ~{2-4%minutes} per side.

Cut quesadillas into thirds and divide between plates. Top with lime crema and @Hot Sauce{1%tsp} to taste. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.